World Again Split on Two ‘Eids’
Saudi Arabia announced Eid-ul-Fitr falls today, while most of Pakistan and India will wait until tomorrow.
It’s a normal occurrence that the Muslim world celebrates Eid-ul-Fitr, which marks the end of the Muslim fasting month of Ramadan, on different days, and we explained why yesterday.
Saudi Arabia last night said the new moon which marks the end of Ramadan was visible and so today is Eid-ul-Fitr.